Walkabout Resources has advised that mining of graphite ore has commenced at Lindi Jumbo with the first blast completed within the starter pit. Walkabout Resources’ CEO, Andrew Cunningham commented: “The first blast and mining of the starter pit area is a new chapter in the development of the Lindi Jumbo Graphite Mine and for Africa, as it also represents the commencement of the first high-grade, large-flake stockpile of responsibly sourced graphite in Tanzania. The effort and expertise put in by our earthmoving contractor TNR, as well as our Lindi Jumbo team on site to conduct the inaugural blast in a safe and controlled operation was a proud moment for all involved.” Mining has commenced at @LindiJumbo following the first blast taking place at the mine area’s starter pit.#WKT CEO Andrew Cunningham commented “The first blast & mining of the starter pit area are significant milestones in the development of #LindiJumbo."https://t.co/Iegyvjh7ip pic.twitter.com/CRIyzpS8w4 Despite delay in the drawdown of @LindiJumbo’s USD20m project debt facility, #WKT is pleased to announce major contractors are continuing site works. Acquisition & manufacturing of critical processing equipment in China is also nearing completion. More: https://t.co/G0v2qpg4Nf pic.twitter.com/WLLo6H8DTr